{{Infobox person | name = Abd Traore | image = Abd Traore.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = 8th December | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Entrepreneur | years_active = | employer = | organization = [[WatsUp TV]] | salary = | net_worth = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | relations = [[Iya Traore]], Abou Traore | awards = | yearsactive = | domesticpartner = | URL = }}
'''Abd Traore''' is a Guinean<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ameyawdebrah.com/watsup-tv-officially-launched-guinea-conakry/|title=WatsUp TV has officially launched in Guinea Conakry - AmeyawDebrah.Com|date=25 July 2016|publisher=}}</ref> entertainment entrepreneur and television executive who is founder and CEO of WatsUp Co, 369 Live and Shob Group.
==Early life== Abd Traore was born in the [[Lagos]] state of Nigeria but grew up and schooled in [[Kuala Lumpur]], Malaysia. He moved to Ghana in 2010 where he had a special training at IPMC.
==Career== He is the CEO of WatsUp Co, the entertainment company that produces [[WatsUp TV]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.modernghana.com/entertainment/37925/watsup-tv-officially-launched-in-guinea-conakry.html|title=Watsup TV Officially Launched In Guinea Conakry|first=Prince|last=Akpah|publisher=}}</ref> and organises the annual [[WatsUp TV Africa Music Video Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201610110051.html|title=Rwanda: Knowles' Video Nominated At Watsup TV Africa Music Video Awards|first=Eddie|last=Nsabimana|date=11 October 2016|publisher=|via=AllAfrica}}</ref> which recognises African Music Videos and Artistes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/DJ-Arafat-Ouder-1er-pick-2016-WatsUp-TV-Music-Video-Awards-522766|title=DJ Arafat & Ouder 1er pick 2016 WatsUp TV Music Video Awards|website=www.ghanaweb.com}}</ref> He has produced WatsUp TV which is noted be a leading pan-African TV Show across the continent airing on DSTV & Canal+ Channels. In 2016, his show ranked as the Most Influential TV Show in Ghana in the annual Ghana Social Media Rankings.<ref>http://cliqafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/2016-Final-Ghana-Social-Media-Rankings-Report-03-02-CliQAfrica-Ltd.pdf</ref>
In 2018 March ,he launched his first Entertainment Music Magazine named WatsUp Magazine, which was covered by Afro beat highlife Ghanian Artist [[Bisa Kdei]].<ref>http://www.pulse.com.gh/lifestyle/events/bisa-kdei-becomes-first-celebrity-to-cover-watsup-magazine-id8129081.html</ref>
==Recognition== In 2017, Busy JUMP<ref>{{cite web|url=https://jump.com.gh/entrepreneurship/abd-traore-media-entrepreneur-on-the-rise|title=ABD Traore - media entrepreneur on the rise|website=JUMP}}</ref> referred to him as a rising media entrepreneur, and he was also nominated for the prestigious [[Africa Youth Awards]] in the Media Personality of the year category. WatsUp TV has also consistently being nominated in the Ghana Startup Awards organised by The African Network of Entrepreneur and [[Jack Daniel's]] Ghana Nightlife Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyguideafrica.com/jack-daniels-launches-nightlife-award-ghana/|title=Jack Daniels Launches Nightlife Award In Ghana - Daily Guide Africa|website=dailyguideafrica.com}}</ref>
