'''''Beverage Digest''''' founded by Jesse Meyers, is a privately owned publication covering the global non-alcoholic [[beverage industry]]. It is free of advertising, relying on subscription revenue. The newsletter was founded in 1982 and publishes 22 regular issues a year. The publisher is based in [[Bedford Hills, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.list-company.com/company-info/4028809a13dd74c80113dd9ba0233ef9/Beverage-Digest-News-Media-New-York-USA.shtml|title=Beverage Digest|publisher=list-company.com|accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref>
''Beverage Digest'' organizes conferences each year, where senior executives in the industry share their view on trends.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beverage-digest.com/conference/fstop.html |title=Future Smarts - December 14, 2009 |work=Beverage Digest |accessdate=2009-08-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090714134145/http://www.beverage-digest.com/conference/fstop.html |archivedate=2009-07-14 |df= }}</ref> Beverage manufacturers often quote information from the annual ''Beverage Digest Fact Book'' and the twice-monthly ''Beverage Digest'' newsletter in their press releases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wiredprnews.com/2009/04/21/pepsico-six-billion-dollar-bid_200904213287.html|title=PepsiCo Six Billion Dollar Bid|work=Wired PR News|date=2009-04-21|accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allbusiness.com/consumer-products/food-beverage-products-nonalcoholics/5429211-1.html|title=XStream Beverage Network, Inc.'s Chinese Rocket Fuel Blasts Off in the Big Apple; Company...|work=Business Wire|date=August 2, 2006|accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.frsplus.com/news/releases/20070606-OAK.asp|title=Press Release: NEW SUN NUTRITION , INC. ANNOUNCES $25 MILLION SERIES A PREFERRED INVESTMENT ROUND LED BY OAK INVESTMENT PARTNERS.|work=New Sun Nutrition|date=June 6, 2007|accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref>
Although the newsletter is written for executives in the [[soft drink|non-alcoholic drinks]] industry, its articles are often cited in publications with a broader audience. ''[[The New York Times]]'' has based a number of articles in part on information first published by ''Beverage Digest''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1986/10/01/business/two-finalists-reported-in-bidding-war-for-7-up.html |title=TWO FINALISTS REPORTED IN BIDDING WAR FOR 7-UP |date=October 1, 1986 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 | first=Richard W. | last=Stevenson}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/01/31/business/new-beverage-from-snapple-seeks-to-avoid-stigma-of-dieting.html?sec=health |title=New Beverage From Snapple Seeks to Avoid Stigma of Dieting |date=January 31, 2003 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 | first=Sherri | last=Day}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://topics.nytimes.com/topics/reference/timestopics/subjects/w/water/bottled_water/index.html |title=Bottled Water |date=August 27, 2009 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 | first=Scott | last=James}}</ref> The [[Los Angeles Times]] also cites the magazine as an authority in various stories.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://latimes.perfectmarket.com/1997-01-24/business/fi-21741_1_taco-bell |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130131073054/http://latimes.perfectmarket.com/1997-01-24/business/fi-21741_1_taco-bell |dead-url=yes |archive-date=January 31, 2013 |title=A Pepsi Challenge |date=January 24, 1997 |publisher=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2007/jan/29/business/ft-yogurt29 |title=Pushing yogurt as a beauty beverage |date=January 29, 2007 |publisher=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 }} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jul/09/business/fi-water9 |title=Stricter labeling urged for bottled water |date=July 9, 2009 |publisher=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=2009-08-27 }} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref> [[Forbes magazine]], [[Yahoo! News]] and [[Reuters]] have also quoted the magazine.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/feeds/afx/2009/03/30/afx6229950.html |publisher=Forbes |title=BRIEF-Beverage digest says U.S. carbonated soft drink market declined 3 percent in 2008 |date=2009-03-30 |accessdate=2009-08-27 }} {{Dead link|date=April 2014|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/137/20090825/371/tbs-analysis-sugar-guidelines-could-hurt.html |title=ANALYSIS - Sugar guidelines could hurt soft drink firms |publisher=Yahoo! News |date=Aug 25, 2009 |accessdate=2009-08-27}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS224177+12-May-2009+PRN20090512 |title=Beverage Industry Fighting Childhood Obesity by Helping Children Balance Calories |date=May 12, 2009 |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref> [[USA Today]] often bases stories on information first published in Beverage Digest.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://content.usatoday.com/topics/topic/Beverage+Digest |title=Beverage Digest |publisher=USA Today |accessdate=2009-08-27}}</ref>
