'''Sidney James van den Bergh''' (25 October 1898, [[Rotterdam]] – 25 September 1977, [[Wassenaar]]) was a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] businessman, World War II military officer and politician, who was a senior manager of [[Unilever]] and [[Ministry of Defence (Netherlands)|Minister of Defence]] for the Netherlands in 1959.
